        giant cell layer. This restricted distribution of 
        Tnfrh1 -positive cells was observed
        both at <NUMEX TYPE="CARDINAL">10.5</NUMEX> <ENAMEX TYPE="ORGANIZATION">dpc</ENAMEX>, when the definitive placental layers have
        recently formed, and at <NUMEX TYPE="CARDINAL">12.5</NUMEX> <ENAMEX TYPE="ORGANIZATION">dpc</ENAMEX>, after these layers have
        begun to mature (<ENAMEX TYPE="PERSON">Fig</ENAMEX>. 6a,6b<NUMEX TYPE="CARDINAL">,6</NUMEX>c). At high magnification, the
        
        Tnfrh1 -positive cells were seen
