        possibility of <ENAMEX TYPE="SUBSTANCE">genomic</ENAMEX> contamination (<ENAMEX TYPE="PERSON">Fig</ENAMEX>. 1b). Since one
        of the <ENAMEX TYPE="ORGANIZATION">SNPs</ENAMEX> that distinguished the standard <NUMEX TYPE="CARDINAL">C57BL/6</NUMEX>
        laboratory strain from the divergent strain 
        <ENAMEX TYPE="PERSON">M. m.</ENAMEX> castaneus (<ENAMEX TYPE="ORGANIZATION">CAST</ENAMEX>) created an 
        <ENAMEX TYPE="LAW">Mbo II</ENAMEX> restriction site in the CAST
        <ENAMEX TYPE="PERSON">sequence</ENAMEX>, we used RFLP analysis to assess allelic
        representation in cDNAs from F1 <ENAMEX TYPE="PER_DESC">progeny</ENAMEX> of <ENAMEX TYPE="PRODUCT">BL/6 × CAST</ENAMEX> and
        <ENAMEX TYPE="PRODUCT">CAST × BL/6</ENAMEX> reciprocal crosses. This indicated an obvious
